# Normalize line endings: store text as LF in git and check out LF on every
# platform. Without this, Windows checkouts (core.autocrlf=true) get CRLF in the
# working tree, which makes `prettier --check` / `pnpm format:check` fail locally
# even though the committed files are LF and Linux CI passes.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be line-ending normalized.
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ico binary
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.pdf binary
